(116, '95c1527a-7bf0-4836-a7f9-46cfefd4a32a', 1, 'Update', 'App\\Models\\Blog', 1, 'App\\Models\\Blog', 1, 'App\\Models\\Blog', 1, '', 'finished', '', '2022-03-06 15:04:09', '2022-03-06 15:04:09', '{\"content\":\"<p><\\/p><img src=\\\"https:\\/\\/digiuth.com\\/uploads\\/digiuth.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" title=\\\"\\\" tt-mode=\\\"file\\\" tt-link-url=\\\"\\\" tt-link-target=\\\"\\\" tt-link-mode=\\\"url\\\" class=\\\"\\\"><p>Music is such an essential part of every human being\'s livelihood that we could never imagine a world without it. Could you imagine a movie without a score and soundtrack? Surely no. But music isn\'t as easy of a concept as we might think. There\'re many layers and complexities within itself that many scientists have researched and discovered a lot of exciting features. Today I want to touch on several interesting aspects of music that researches uncovered <mark>throughout <\\/mark>the years. Let\'s dive in!<br><br><\\/p><p><br>Mental Health<br><br><\\/p><p>Barry Goldstein, a recording artist who has studied the vibrational effects of music for more than 25 years, says music has a profound impact on the brain. In <a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.consciouslifestylemag.com\\/music-and-the-brain-affects-mood\\/\\\" tt-mode=\\\"url\\\">a column<\\/a> for Conscious Lifestyle magazine, Goldstein wrote that music could enhance brain functions. He said music could evoke emotion, help regain memories, stimulate new neural connections, and active attention.<br><br><\\/p><img src=\\\"https:\\/\\/digiuth.com\\/uploads\\/digiuth.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" title=\\\"\\\" tt-mode=\\\"file\\\" tt-link-url=\\\"\\\" tt-link-target=\\\"\\\" tt-link-mode=\\\"url\\\" class=\\\"\\\"><p>Therefore, there were <a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.frontiersin.org\\/articles\\/10.3389\\/fpsyg.2019.01199\\/full\\\" tt-mode=\\\"url\\\">researches<\\/a> made on people with symptoms of depression, where the results of listening to music during mentally tough times could have had very different effects depending on the person. The mood changes for better or worse also depends on the person\'s ability to choose the right type of music for those situations, which we will later touch on in this article. This basically means music is a double-edged sword that should be handled carefully. And to give examples on music genres affecting the mental state, the researchers showed how classical and relaxing music increased positive moods, <a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\\/pubmed\\/20013543\\\" tt-mode=\\\"url\\\">techno and heavy metal brought people down<\\/a> even more.<br><br><\\/p><img src=\\\"https:\\/\\/digiuth.com\\/uploads\\/digiuth.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" title=\\\"\\\" tt-mode=\\\"file\\\" tt-link-url=\\\"\\\" tt-link-target=\\\"\\\" tt-link-mode=\\\"url\\\" class=\\\"\\\"><p><br>Hormones<br><br><\\/p><p>During the studies, scientists have shown that music also has a direct effect on our hormones; many even consider it as a natural antidepressant! Why? Because specific tunes and sounds can cause the release of serotonin and dopamine (neurotransmitters) in the brain, which leads to increased feelings of happiness and well-being. It also releases norepinephrine, which is a hormone that invokes feelings of euphoria.<br><br><\\/p><img src=\\\"https:\\/\\/digiuth.com\\/uploads\\/digiuth.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" title=\\\"\\\" tt-mode=\\\"file\\\" tt-link-url=\\\"\\\" tt-link-target=\\\"\\\" tt-link-mode=\\\"url\\\" class=\\\"\\\"><p><br>Insomnia<br><br><\\/p><p>More than <a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.who.int\\/en\\/news-room\\/fact-sheets\\/detail\\/depression\\\" tt-mode=\\\"url\\\">264 million<\\/a> people suffer from depression around the world, and <a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\\/pmc\\/articles\\/PMC3108260\\/\\\" tt-mode=\\\"url\\\">90%<\\/a> of them also experience insomnia. The above research also found that symptoms of depression only decreased in the group that listened to classical or relaxing music before going to bed.<br><br><\\/p><p><br>Musical Awareness<br><br><\\/p><p>We saw that the different types of music could affect people differently, but then there comes the question: how could I choose wisely? You need to be self-aware! I call this concept the musical awareness, which means you will not worsen your mental state by listening to inappropriate tunes when you shouldn\'t. It also directly ties into emotional awareness, or the ability to identify personal experiences, which can be a protective factor against psychopathology by allowing an individual to recognize the need to activate appropriate emotion regulation strategies.<br><br><\\/p><img src=\\\"https:\\/\\/digiuth.com\\/uploads\\/digiuth.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" title=\\\"\\\" tt-mode=\\\"file\\\" tt-link-url=\\\"\\\" tt-link-target=\\\"\\\" tt-link-mode=\\\"url\\\" class=\\\"\\\"><p>Experiments were conducted on seven young people with symptoms of depression. I don\'t want to bother you with unnecessary details so I will cut to two main sections of the experiments. (you can read the whole experiment <a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.frontiersin.org\\/articles\\/10.3389\\/fpsyg.2019.01199\\/full\\\" tt-mode=\\\"url\\\">here<\\/a>)<br><br><\\/p><img src=\\\"https:\\/\\/digiuth.com\\/uploads\\/digiuth.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" title=\\\"\\\" tt-mode=\\\"file\\\" tt-link-url=\\\"\\\" tt-link-target=\\\"\\\" tt-link-mode=\\\"url\\\" class=\\\"\\\"><p><br><br><\\/p>\"}', '{\"content\":\"<p><\\/p><img src=\\\"https:\\/\\/digiuth.com\\/uploads\\/digiuth.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" title=\\\"\\\" tt-mode=\\\"file\\\" tt-link-url=\\\"\\\" tt-link-target=\\\"\\\" tt-link-mode=\\\"url\\\" class=\\\"\\\"><p>Music is such an essential part of every human being\'s livelihood that we could never imagine a world without it. Could you imagine a movie without a score and soundtrack? Surely no. But music isn\'t as easy of a concept as we might think.